# Onshape Export & Translation

Two ways to get geometry **out** of Onshape in a foreign format. **Synchronous
direct exports** are plain GETs on a Part Studio or Part (`/stl`, `/parasolid`,
`/gltf`, `/shadedviews`) — the file streams back in the response body, no job to
track. **Asynchronous translation** is a job: POST a translation request naming a
target `formatName` (STEP, IGES, SOLIDWORKS, ACIS, PDF, DWG, RHINO…), receive a
translation `id` + state, poll `GET /translations/{tid}` until the state is `DONE`,
then download the produced foreign-data / blob element. The same translation
endpoint also handles **import** (uploading a foreign CAD file *into* Onshape).
Sibling exports live on @onshape/partstudios, @onshape/parts, @onshape/drawings;
results land as elements you read via @onshape/elements.

## Model

- Sync vs async, the dividing line:
  - **Sync** = format the server can tessellate/serialize cheaply and stream:
    STL, Parasolid (`.x_t`/`.x_b`), glTF, shaded PNGs. Endpoint *is* the format.
    Response is the file (`application/octet-stream` for STL, `model/gltf+json`
    for glTF, base64 image strings for shaded views). One request, done.
  - **Async** = a translator job for heavy/foreign formats (STEP/IGES/SOLIDWORKS/
    DWG/PDF…). You POST a request and get back a translation record, not the file.
- Path coordinate (shared did/wid/eid model, see @onshape/auth):
  - Sync exports accept the read family `…/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}` — `wvm`
    is `w`/`v`/`m`, so you can export from a workspace, version, or microversion.
    A part-level export adds `/partid/{partid}`.
  - Creating a translation **writes** (it can store the result back in the doc), so
    `POST /translations/d/{did}/w/{wid}` targets a **workspace**. Listing is by
    document `GET /translations/d/{did}`; status/delete are by translation id.
- **Translation state machine** — `requestState` (BTTranslationRequestState):
  `ACTIVE` → terminal `DONE` or `FAILED`. Poll `GET /translations/{tid}` on an
  interval; on `FAILED` read `failureReason`. There is no callback in this slice
  (the request body's `notifyUser` only emails); poll to learn completion.
- **Getting the bytes after DONE** — the response carries result pointers, not the
  file. Two cases:
  - `storeInDocument: true` → result is a new element/tab in the doc; read
    `resultElementIds` (+ `resultDocumentId`/`resultWorkspaceId`/`versionId`) and
    open it as a @onshape/elements blob.
  - `storeInDocument: false` → result is foreign data; read
    `resultExternalDataIds` and download each blob (the external-data download
    endpoint is owned by @onshape/documents / @onshape/elements, not this slice).
- **Thumbnails** are a parallel "give me an image" family: `GET /thumbnails/d/{did}…`
  returns either a JSON `sizes`/`secondarySizes` info structure (which sizes exist)
  or, on the `…/s/{sz}` and `…/e/{eid}/…/s/{sz}` paths, the raw image bytes
  (`application/octet-stream`). Use these for a quick preview without a full export.
- **Export rules** name and organize exported files; `GET /exportrules/options/
  {cu}/{cuid}` lists the valid rule options for a user or company (`cu` = `users`
  or `companies`, `cuid` = that id). A translation echoes the applied rule back as
  `exportRuleFileName`.

## Endpoints

Asynchronous translation (this slice):

| METHOD path | purpose |
|---|---|
| `POST /translations/d/{did}/w/{wid}` | create a translation/import job (multipart) |
| `GET /translations/{tid}` | status of one translation (poll this) |
| `GET /translations/d/{did}` | list a document's translations (offset/limit) |
| `DELETE /translations/{tid}` | delete a translation request |
| `GET /translations/translationformats` | list all supported source/dest formats |

Synchronous direct exports (folded in from @onshape/partstudios, @onshape/parts):

| METHOD path | purpose |
|---|---|
| `GET /partstudios/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/stl` | stream a Part Studio as STL |
| `GET /partstudios/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/parasolid` | stream as Parasolid |
| `GET /partstudios/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/gltf` | stream as glTF (`model/gltf+json`) |
| `GET /partstudios/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/shadedviews` | base64 PNG shaded views |
| `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/stl` | one part as STL |
| `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/parasolid` | one part as Parasolid |
| `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/gltf` | one part as glTF |
| `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/shadedviews` | one part shaded views |

> There is also an async export family on Part Studios — `POST …/e/{eid}/export/
> {step,gltf,obj,translations}` — that returns the same translation record and is
> the format-rich alternative to the sync GETs; it lives in @onshape/partstudios.

Thumbnails & export rules (this slice):

| METHOD path | purpose |
|---|---|
| `GET /thumbnails/d/{did}` | thumbnail info (sizes) for the default workspace |
| `GET /thumbnails/d/{did}/w/{wid}` · `…/v/{vid}` | info for a workspace / version |
| `GET /thumbnails/d/{did}/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}` | thumbnail info for one element |
| `GET /thumbnails/d/{did}/w/{wid}/s/{sz}` | document image bytes at size `sz` |
| `GET /thumbnails/d/{did}/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}/s/{sz}` | element image bytes at size |
| `GET /thumbnails/d/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}/ac/{cid}/s/{sz}` | element image for a configuration |
| `GET /exportrules/options/{cu}/{cuid}` | valid export-rule options for user/company |

Sizes use `{sz}` like `300x300`; the info responses list which sizes exist.
Skip the deprecated `/thumbnails/document/{did}` aliases — use `/thumbnails/d/…`.

## Shapes

Create-translation request (multipart/form-data; meaningful fields). The same body
serves export *and* import — for an export you set the target `formatName` and the
source ids; `file`/`encodedFilename`/`import*` apply to the upload-in direction:

```jsonc
// POST /translations/d/{did}/w/{wid}   (multipart/form-data)
{
  "formatName": "STEP",          // target (or source) format: STEP/IGES/SOLIDWORKS/PARASOLID/ACIS/…
  "storeInDocument": false,      // true → write result as a doc element; false → external blob
  "notifyUser": false,           // email the user on completion (not a programmatic callback)
  "flattenAssemblies": false,
  "createComposite": false,
  // --- import direction (uploading a foreign file INTO Onshape) ---
  "file": "<binary>",
  "encodedFilename": "bracket.step",
  "importWithinDocument": true,
  "importAppearances": true,
  "splitAssembliesIntoMultipleDocuments": false,
  "locationElementId": "", "ownerId": "", "parentId": ""
}
```

Translation status / create response (`GET /translations/{tid}` and the POST
return the same shape — trimmed to the load-bearing fields):

```jsonc
// resp: application/json
{
  "id": "5f...e1",                 // translation id — poll GET /translations/{id}
  "requestState": "ACTIVE",        // BTTranslationRequestState: ACTIVE → DONE | FAILED
  "failureReason": "",             // populated when requestState == FAILED
  "name": "Part Studio 1 STEP",
  "exportRuleFileName": "...",     // applied export-rule name, if any
  // result pointers — read whichever matches storeInDocument:
  "resultExternalDataIds": ["6a..."],   // storeInDocument=false → download these blobs
  "resultElementIds": ["..."],          // storeInDocument=true  → new element(s) in the doc
  "resultDocumentId": "...", "resultWorkspaceId": "...", "versionId": "...",
  "documentId": "378e93b0ad360aa043a0220b", "workspaceId": "09273312fedee7bf3c3482ad",
  "requestElementId": "a77918b06d5131918477a269", "href": "https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10/translations/5f...e1"
}
```

Thumbnail info (the JSON, non-image, variant):

```jsonc
// GET /thumbnails/d/{did}/w/{wid}
{ "id": "...", "href": "...",
  "sizes": [ { /* BTThumbnailSizeInfo: size, href, mediaType, … per spec */ } ],
  "secondarySizes": [[ /* per-configuration size lists */ ]] }
```

## Recipe

Synchronous STL export — the simplest end-to-end proof. READ-ONLY (a GET; it
streams the model, changes nothing). Basic auth (see @onshape/auth)
(`$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY` over HTTPS, local testing only — use
HMAC for production, see @onshape/auth). Uses the kb2 sample ids.

```bash
# ids from the kb2 sample document
DID=378e93b0ad360aa043a0220b
WID=09273312fedee7bf3c3482ad
EID=a77918b06d5131918477a269
BASE=https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10

# sync STL export — streams the file straight back (no job, no polling)
curl -sS -L -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  -H 'Accept: application/octet-stream' \
  "$BASE/partstudios/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/stl?mode=text&units=millimeter" \
  -o partstudio.stl

# VERIFY: 200 + the body is an ASCII STL (starts with "solid", ends with "endsolid")
code=$(curl -sS -L -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' \
  -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  "$BASE/partstudios/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/stl?mode=text&units=millimeter")
head -c5 partstudio.stl | grep -q '^solid' \
  && grep -q 'endsolid' partstudio.stl \
  && [ "$code" = 200 ] \
  && echo "OK: STL exported ($code)" || echo "FAIL ($code)"
```

> `mode=binary` returns a binary STL instead (verify on size/`%{http_code}` only,
> not on the `solid`/`endsolid` text markers). For STEP/IGES/etc. there is no sync
> GET — POST `/translations/d/{did}/w/{wid}` with `formatName`, then poll
> `GET /translations/{id}` until `requestState == "DONE"` and download
> `resultExternalDataIds`.

See @onshape/partstudios and @onshape/parts for the full sync-export param set
(`partIds`, `configuration`, tolerances), @onshape/drawings for drawing exports
(DWG/DXF/PDF), @onshape/elements for opening a stored translation result, and
@onshape/auth for HMAC signing. UI fallback: @onshape/playwright.
